   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">If boost charge is enabled the system will
charge the batteries with the boost charge voltage instead of the
float charge voltage for a predefined time.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">To enable/disable
boost charge:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>. </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow keys</b> to navigate to <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Boost charge</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To enable: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number 1 key</b> to turn
on boost charge.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To disable: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Star/number
0 key</b> to turn off boost charge.</p>
                     <note class="- topic/note ">On the mimic diagram,
the yellow rectifier LED will indicate that boost charge is active.</note>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The system will only apply boost charge for a set time, between
0 and 99 hours (default setting is 8 hours). To change this setting
please contact your local <xref conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Reality_service_centers"
                              scope="local"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> or wait 30 seconds to exit the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
